items.title: D-backs shut out Rockies behind Godley's gem
items.summary: Zack Godley delivered his longest outing of the year on Thursday, and was backed by a five-run Arizona first inning as the D-backs shut out the Rockies, 7-0, at Chase Field.
items.content: Zack Godley delivered his longest outing of the year on Thursday, and was backed by a five-run Arizona first inning as the D-backs shut out the Rockies, 7-0, at Chase Field.

items.title: Harper takes next step in recovery by running
items.summary: Bryce Harper continues to progress as he aims to return to the Nationals in time for the postseason. The latest step came on the warning track at Nationals Park prior to Thursday's game against the Braves.
items.content: Bryce Harper continues to progress as he aims to return to the Nationals in time for the postseason. The latest step came on the warning track at Nationals Park prior to Thursday's game against the Braves.

items.title: Marisnick out 6-8 weeks with fractured thumb
items.summary: Astros center fielder Jake Marisnick is likely to miss the rest of the season, including the playoffs, after suffering a fractured right thumb sliding into second base in the third inning of Wednesday's 9-1 loss to the Angels.
items.content: Astros center fielder Jake Marisnick is likely to miss the rest of the season, including the playoffs, after suffering a fractured right thumb sliding into second base in the third inning of Wednesday's 9-1 loss to the Angels.

items.title: Astros' Fiers handed 5-game suspension
items.summary: Astros pitcher Mike Fiers has received a five-game suspension and an undisclosed fine for intentionally throwing a pitch in the area of the head of Luis Valbuena of the Angels in the bottom of the fourth inning of Wednesday evening's game at Angel Stadium.

items.title: Slugger Davis away on paternity leave
items.summary: Khris Davis' attempt at a second consecutive 40-homer season is on hold, and for good reason.
